# Validation and Runtime Safety

- Label validation as one of: runtime-verified, static-only, or speculative.
- Never present speculative claims as verified facts.
- For runtime-impacting changes, report:
  - commands run
  - outcomes
  - explicit unverified items
- Use these docs as canonical validation sources:
  - `docs/ai/VALIDATION_POLICY.md`
  - `docs/ai/VALIDATION_STANDARD.md`
  - `docs/ai/REGRESSION_CHECKLIST.md`

# Runtime Safety Boundaries

- In workflow/docs tasks, do not alter gameplay runtime logic.
- If runtime checks are not run, say so directly and avoid certainty claims.
- Do not regress flow/readability constraints while validating docs or config changes.
